# 🔍 Detection Rule: Impossible Travel (Geolocation Anomaly)

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 1. Objective

Detect impossible travel scenarios where a user logs in from
geographically distant locations within a short time period, indicating
potential account compromise.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 2. Log Sources

-   Azure AD Sign-in Logs
-   Okta Authentication Logs
-   VPN Logs
-   Cloud Application Logs

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 3. Detection Logic

Trigger alert when:

-   Same user logs in from two distant locations
-   Time difference makes travel physically impossible
-   IP addresses belong to different geolocations

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 4. Detection Queries

### KQL

    SigninLogs
    | summarize Locations = make_set(Location), IPs = make_set(IPAddress), count() by UserPrincipalName, bin(TimeGenerated, 1h)
    | where array_length(Locations) > 1

------------------------------------------------------------------------

### Splunk

    index=signin_logs
    | stats values(src_ip) as ips, values(location) as locations by user
    | where mvcount(locations) > 1

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 5. Tuning & Thresholds

-   Adjust time window (30 min to 2 hours)
-   Exclude known VPN/proxy IPs
-   Consider corporate network locations
-   Use geo-distance calculation if available

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 6. False Positives

-   VPN usage
-   Mobile network switching
-   Corporate proxy routing
-   Cloud services using distributed IPs

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 7. Severity

-   Low: Known VPN usage
-   Medium: Location anomaly without suspicious activity
-   High: New location + suspicious activity
-   Critical: Confirmed account compromise

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 8. MITRE ATT&CK Mapping

-   T1078 --- Valid Accounts

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 9. Analyst Notes

Impossible travel alerts are often noisy.

Key checks:

-   Same device vs different device
-   VPN vs unknown IP
-   MFA usage
-   User behavior after login

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 10. Recommended Response

-   Verify with user
-   Reset password if needed
-   Revoke active sessions
-   Enforce MFA
-   Monitor account activity

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## 11. Improvements

-   Add device fingerprinting
-   Correlate with MFA logs
